      "summary": "Record op-level timing and memory traces from the C++ engine.",
      "extended": "Drives the engine's profiling hook so that every dispatched op\nbecomes an `OpEvent`. Suitable for both interactive use\n(`with` block) and programmatic control via explicit\n`start` / `stop`. Recorded events can be exported as a\nChrome / Perfetto trace for visual inspection.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "with_memory",
          "annotation": "bool",
          "description": "If `True` (default), also capture allocator stats via\n`MemoryStats`.",
          "default": "True"
        }
      ],
      "returns": null,
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        ">>> import lucid\n>>> with lucid.profiler.profile() as prof:\n...     y = lucid.randn(64, 64) @ lucid.randn(64, 64)\n>>> top = prof.key_averages()[:5]"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Total recorded time can be summarised per op as\n\n$$\nT_{\\text{op}} = \\sum_{i : \\text{name}(e_i) = \\text{op}} t_i,\n$$\nvia `key_averages`. Only one `Profiler` may be active\nat a time; entering a nested instance overwrites the engine's\ncurrent profiler pointer until the outer context exits."
      ],
      "attributes": [],
      "warns": [],
      "see_also": []
    },
    {
      "name": "profile",
      "path": "lucid.profiler.profile",
      "kind": "function",
      "labels": [],
      "signature": "profile(activities: list[str] | None = None, with_memory: bool = True)",
      "source": "https://github.com/ChanLumerico/lucid/blob/dbb2f29b4/lucid/profiler/__init__.py#L337",
      "subcategory": null,
      "summary": "Context manager that records ops executed within the `with` block.",
      "extended": "The canonical entry point for ad-hoc profiling: enter the context,\nrun any Lucid computation, exit, then inspect `prof.events()` or\n`prof.key_averages()`. The `activities` parameter is accepted\nfor parity with the conventional profiling API but is not\ninterpreted.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "activities",
          "annotation": "list of str",
          "description": "Currently ignored; reserved for future per-device filtering.",
          "default": "None"
        },
        {
          "name": "with_memory",
          "annotation": "bool",
          "description": "Include memory statistics in the recorded trace. Default\n`True`.",
          "default": "True"
        }
      ],
      "returns": {
        "annotation": "Iterator[Profiler]",
        "description": ""
      },
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        ">>> import lucid\n>>> with lucid.profiler.profile() as prof:\n...     out = lucid.randn(128, 128) @ lucid.randn(128, 128)\n>>> for row in prof.key_averages():\n...     print(row)"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Internally instantiates a `Profiler` and routes its lifecycle\nthrough `__enter__` / `__exit__`. Equivalent to::\n\n    prof = Profiler(with_memory=with_memory)\n    prof.start()\n    try: ...\n    finally: prof.stop()"
      ],
      "attributes": [],
      "warns": [],
      "see_also": []
    },
